programme.title: One Track Back
programme.desc: Follow Matthias Walkner through a journey of rehab and redemption as he overcomes injury and returns to form. Matthias Walkner, the daredevil in the world of rally raid biking, made the impossible possible: after a heavy crash at the 2016 Dakar Rally, sidelining his career, he gets crowned Dakar Rally champion only two years later.

programme.title: Game Loading
programme.desc: Disrupting the big-budget games industry, indie developers have impacted the world of video games in a big way. Explore the world of indie game developers – their craft, their games, their dreams and the way that these small teams of artists and programmers have forever changed not only video game culture, but the world at large.

programme.title: Human Dart
programme.desc: A skydiver goes high and long to set the world record for the farthest absolute distance flown in a wingsuit. Skydiver Andy Stumpf loves a challenge, so when he has the opportunity to break four world records in one shot, he jumps at the chance. But what he wants above all else is to break the record for the farthest absolute distance flown in a wingsuit.

programme.title: Racing Together
programme.desc: The history of motorcycle racing is charted through its best riders, from former legends to today’s stars. Discover the history of motorcycle racing through its key personalities, from former legends to today’s multi-title-winning, globetrotting riders, such as Mick Doohan, Valentino Rossi and Marc Márquez.

programme.title: Life Beyond Earth
programme.desc: US rapper GZA visits the Mars Desert Research Station in Utah and NASA’s Jet Propulsion lab in California. American rapper GZA reflects on two big issues facing humanity: where we came from and whether we're alone. We’ve searched for answers for hundreds of years here on Earth, but perhaps it's time for us to adjust our gaze to the great beyond.

programme.title: Friday Night Juice
programme.desc: Artists, dancers and DJs in Barcelona's hip-hop scene join forces to put on the best party in the city. Barcelona's hip-hop scene converges twice a month at the best all-night dance party in the city. Juice is an event where people from all backgrounds come to dance, vibe, rap and connect with one another in an inclusive and creative environment.

programme.title: The Blue Armada
programme.desc: An award-winning Russian motorsports team show their unique way of working and preparing for the Dakar Rally. The most famous and award-winning motorsports team in Russia use their unique way of working together to prepare for off-road racing's most prestigious event, the Dakar Rally.

programme.title: The Silent Samurai
programme.sub-title: A look back at Dani Pedrosa's career
programme.desc: Take a look at the key moments that made Dani Pedrosa one of the most talented riders of his generation. Enjoy a look back at Dani Pedrosa’s motorcycling career as seen through the eyes of his coach, friend and former MotoGP star Sete Gibernau. Relive the key moments that made him one of the most talented riders of his generation.

programme.title: Rich + Tone: PolyRhythmic
programme.desc: Choreography team Rich + Tone take it back to their roots as they talk about their career in the dance world. Brothers Richmond and Anthony Talauega have been behind some of pop music's most explosive dance performances. Their inspiration for dancing comes from their heritage and upbringing, which they revisit as they craft a major routine for Chris Brown.

programme.title: What Lies Ahead
programme.desc: The b-boys consider their futures. Roxrite judges a competition. Neguin visits friends. Lilou makes a choice. The b-boys get honest with themselves while setting their future goals. Roxrite judges a BC One qualifier. Neguin takes his nephew to an open b-boy practice session. After some soul-searching, Lilou opts to go for a third world championship.

programme.title: The Learning Curve
programme.sub-title: Drew Bezanson: From BMX to MTB
programme.desc: Drew Bezanson tries to make the transition from freestyle BMX to the world of slopestyle mountain biking. To be a master of two sports is a feat many have tried but few have accomplished. Drew Bezanson is one of the top BMX riders in the world, but now he wants to enter the world of slopestyle mountain biking and compete at Red Bull Joyride.

programme.title: Wingmen
programme.desc: Three elite BASE jumpers face the unknown on a global journey to find the best wingsuit and BASE jump spots. Three of the world's best wingsuit flyers set out on a global journey in search of perfect spots for proximity flying and BASE jumps. From Brazil to China, the trio face some of the most thrilling and challenging flights of their lives.

programme.title: Locked In
programme.sub-title: First descent of the Beriman Gorge
programme.desc: Ben Stookesberry and a group of kayakers attempt a first descent of the Beriman River in Papua New Guinea. Ben Stookesberry and a group of professional kayakers journey to the remote jungles of Papua New Guinea to attempt a first descent of the Beriman River, a daunting 40km run lined with sheer limestone walls and no way out but to ride to the ocean.

programme.title: Rob Meets Sam Sunderland
programme.desc: Rob Warner meets 2017 Dakar Rally winner Sam Sunderland as he hones his motorcycle skills for the 2019 event. Rob Warner heads to France to meet with 2017 Dakar Rally winner Sam Sunderland to see how the British motorcycle rider’s preparations are going for the 2019 edition of the event.
